                        <interp inst="t18540814-name-199" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN FORSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a labourer. On 31st July I was in Lower Thames-street. I saw the prisoner take a handkerchief out of the prosecutor's pocket; he put it under his jacket—I asked the prosecutor if he had lost his handkerchief; he said, "Yes"—I called a policeman, and pointed out the prisoner to him—I saw the policeman go to him, and take the handker<lb></lb>chief from his jacket pocket in Bear-lane.</p>
